        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms across Western Prowers county, moving north at 30 mph.

These storms will affect western Prowers and eastern Kiowa county
through 315 pm

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brandon, Sheridan Lake, Lamar, Bristol, and Granada.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
